.TH "virtqueue_kick_prepare" 9 "virtqueue_kick_prepare" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
virtqueue_kick_prepare \- first half of split virtqueue_kick call.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" virtqueue_kick_prepare
.BI "(struct virtqueue *_vq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "_vq" 12
the struct virtqueue
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Instead of \fBvirtqueue_kick\fP, you can do:
if (virtqueue_kick_prepare(vq))
virtqueue_notify(vq);

This is sometimes useful because the \fBvirtqueue_kick_prepare\fP needs
to be serialized, but the actual \fBvirtqueue_notify\fP call does not.
